<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="237" pageId="5" pageNumber="236" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,2002,2028]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,465]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="237" pageId="5" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,2002,2028]" pageId="5" pageNumber="236">Type data:</emphasis>
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3014903308" collectionCode="MNHP" country="Mexico" county="Friese" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="237" location="In" municipality="Orizaba" pageId="5" pageNumber="236" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="lectotype">
<bibRefCitation author="Friese, H." box="[290,442,2002,2028]" pageId="5" pageNumber="236" pagination="39 - 48" refId="ref21677" refString="Friese, H. (1899) Neue arten der Bienengattungen Epicharis Klug und Centris Fabr. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 23, 39 - 48." type="journal article" year="1899">Friese (1899)</bibRefCitation>
described this species from a very large series of specimens of both sexes collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[151,237,151,177]" name="Mexico" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(Orizaba) and 
<collectingCountry box="[406,478,151,177]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:8422F619C515BD57FF15F8EB5243FE64:095411D4C516BD57FE6AFF3B5097FF04" box="[488,511,151,177]" country="Mexico" county="Friese" municipality="Orizaba" name="In" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">In</location>
1969, 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:8422F619C515BD57FF15F8EB5243FE64:095411D4C516BD57FDCFFF3B53F0FF04" box="[589,664,151,177]" country="Mexico" county="Friese" municipality="Orizaba" name="Moure" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Moure</location>
designated the 
<typeStatus box="[839,945,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">lectotype</typeStatus>
, but he did not provide any data or even the sex of the specimen that help to recognize it. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:8422F619C515BD57FF15F8EB5243FE64:095411D4C516BD57FD11FF1753BBFF60" box="[659,723,187,213]" country="Mexico" county="Friese" municipality="Orizaba" name="Some" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Some</location>
of the specimens from 
<collectingMunicipality box="[986,1075,187,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Orizaba</collectingMunicipality>
studied by 
<collectingCounty box="[1205,1273,187,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Friese</collectingCounty>
were found in the 
<collectionCode box="[191,272,223,249]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/3kvn-7rck" name="Princeton University" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">MNHP</collectionCode>
, but unfortunately, none labeled as 
<typeStatus box="[661,767,223,249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">lectotype</typeStatus>
.Anyway, all those specimens are conspecific and they agree with the current interpretation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Roig-Alsina" authorityYear="2000" baseAuthorityName="Erichson" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[524,615,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varia">
<emphasis box="[524,543,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[556,615,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">varia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
